Document: ParticleProcessMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_particleprocessmaterial.rst
Summary: An overview of the ParticleProcessMaterial class, which is a Material used to define particle behavior for GPUParticles2D and GPUParticles3D nodes.

Inherits: Material < Resource < RefCounted < Object

ParticleProcessMaterial is a Material that can be used to control the behavior of a particle system. It is used by GPUParticles2D and GPUParticles3D nodes. The properties of the ParticleProcessMaterial are used to set the initial values of the particles and to control their behavior over time. A number of these properties are floats, but can be extended to a CurveTexture or a GradientTexture1D (for colors). When a texture is used, the value of the property is determined by the texture at the particle's lifetime.

For a more advanced and flexible way to create particles, you can use a ParticleShader with a ShaderMaterial.
---CHUNK---
